ompanions-study-says-1-in-3-indians-use-agentic-ai-9586588%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20CEO%20pivoting%20my%20business%20abroad%20because%20of%20tariffs.%20I'm%20treating%20the%20US%20like%20hot%20lava.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matthew%20Hassett%20and%20Abbey%20Phaneuf%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690aa709599d46a4ccc17da3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAbbey%20Phaneuf%2C%20marketing%20director%20at%20Loftie%2C%20and%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Matthew%20Hassett%20have%20worked%20to%20pivot%20the%20company%20to%20focus%20on%20sales%20outside%20the%20US.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Loftie%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMatthew%20Hassett%20shifted%20the%20focus%20of%20his%20company%2C%20Loftie%2C%20to%20international%20sales%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftariffs%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebecause%20of%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELoftie's%20sales%20outside%20the%20US%20have%20grown%20from%20about%203%25%20to%20nearly%2050%25%20in%20a%20few%20months%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20manufactures%20in%20China%20and%20is%20now%20treating%20the%20US%20market%20like%20%26quot%3Bhot%20lava%2C%26quot%3B%20Hassett%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-making-ceo-founder-shift-business-model-amid-impact-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMatthew%20Hassett%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Efounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Loftie.%20The%20company%20makes%20its%20products%2C%20including%20a%20digital%20clock%20and%20lamp%20designed%20to%20promote%20sound%20sleep%2C%20in%20China.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20Trump's%20tariffs%2C%20selling%20inside%20the%20US%20has%20become%20more%20expensive%20for%20Loftie.%20To%20boost%20its%20business%2C%20the%20company%20is%20shifting%20its%20focus%20to%20an%20international%20market.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20brevity%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20mid-August%2C%20I%20was%20very%20stressed.%20It%20then%20became%20clear%20that%20our%20plan%20to%20pivot%20from%20the%20US%20to%20more%20international%20sales%20was%20working%20really%20well.%20We're%20now%20almost%2050%25%20international%20sales%20through%20our%20website%20over%20about%20three%20months%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%20about%203%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20really%20is%20as%20simple%20as%20Econ%20101.%20You%20can%20either%20adjust%20supply%20or%20demand.%20Supply%20is%20constrained%20by%20unpredictable%20government%20policy%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20it's%20still%20not%20settled%20at%20the%20peak%20season%2C%20with%20the%20holidays%20coming%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20it%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20move%20our%20manufacturing%2C%20especially%20knowing%20that%20we%20have%20the%20best%20price%20and%20quality%2C%20which%20is%20a%20rare%20combination%2C%20because%20we%20produce%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20a%20pilot%20run%20in%20Thailand.%20But%20it%20costs%2020%25%20more%20because%20they've%20got%20to%20move%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20components%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20Asia%20to%20Thailand.%20The%20labor%20costs%20are%20also%20higher.%20Why%20would%20you%20move%20from%20China%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20try%20to%20worry%20about%20irrational%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EUS%20policy%2C%20we%20just%20focused%20on%20selling%20the%20product%20that%20people%20want%20worldwide%2C%20worldwide.%20We're%20really%20lucky%20to%20have%20a%20product%20that%20works%20in%20other%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20decided%20to%20treat%20the%20US%20like%20hot%20lava%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20touch%20unless%20you%20really%20have%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa258577-5305-4203-841f-88f1c5dd7d6e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoing%20abroad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20always%20put%20off%20selling%20abroad%20because%20I'd%20heard%20in%20a%20business%20school%20class%20to%20start%20with%20the%20US%20market%2C%20because%20it's%20the%20biggest%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BDon't%20waste%20your%20time%20trying%20to%20extend%20your%20operations.%26quot%3B%20I%20think%20that's%20outdated%20advice%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20technology%20and%20logistics%20available%20in%202025.%20I%20wish%20we'd%20done%20it%20sooner%3B%20it's%20just%20so%20much%20more%20stable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20marketing%20costs%20are%20also%20lower%2C%20so%20it%20allows%20us%20to%20offer%20the%20same%20policies%20that%20we%20have%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20free%20shipping%20and%20a%20one-year%20warranty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20been%20such%20a%20relief%2C%20and%20it%20allows%20me%20to%20have%20time%20for%20actually%20thinking%20about%20productive%2C%20exciting%20new%20chapters%20for%20the%20company%20and%20not%20just%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20international%20sales%20strategy%20is%20what%20has%20allowed%20me%20to%20keep%20our%20team.%20We%20only%20have%20US-based%20employees.%20We%20have%20consultants%20in%20other%20places%2C%20but%20just%20a%20handful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20room%20to%20grow%2C%20because%20we%20have%20mostly%20been%20doing%20English-language%20ads.%20The%20UK%20and%20Canada%20have%20been%20the%20most%20successful%2C%20accordingly.%20But%20we're%20working%20on%20creating%20native%20ads%20in%20many%20languages.%20It's%20been%20a%20really%20good%20gamble%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20provided%20a%20lot%20of%20relief%20and%20stability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2203f3ce5b-8b53-4ccf-8363-b36e2d227d77%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESigns%20of%20success%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20about%20two%20months%20to%20see%20that%20this%20plan%20was%20working.%20We%20still%20had%20the%20US%20sales.%20But%20the%20summer%20was%20terrible%20just%20because%2C%20at%20one%20point%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20we%20had%20tariffs%20of%20175%25%20to%20180%25%20on%20our%20products.%20So%20we%20couldn't%20move%20any%20new%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20we%20had%20some%20inventory%20left%20in%20the%20US%20that%20we%20had%20paid%20the%20duties%20on%20before%20the%20tariffs%20escalated.%20That%20provided%20some%20buffer%20time%20to%20try%20out%20this%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hope%20that%20international%20sales%20can%20mean%20a%20doubling%20of%20our%20revenue%20globally%2C%20and%20that%20eventually%20there%20is%20stability%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20we%20can%20sell%20more%20here%20again%20%E2%80%94%20but%20I%20have%20no%20idea.%20I'm%20just%20taking%20it%20day%20by%20day%2C%20because%20that's%20how%20volatile%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20summer%2C%20I%20was%20writing%20about%20this%2C%20and%20how%20it's%20existential%20to%20our%20company.%20That%20was%20really%20bad%20for%20my%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20I%20could%20do%20to%20control%20it.%20The%20thing%20that's%20a%20huge%20relief%20to%20me%20is%20that%20we%20haven't%20had%20to%20lay%20anyone%20off%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20see%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployers-laying-off-workers-in-waves-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elayoffs%20with%20AI%20at%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20have%20no%20plans%20to%20lay%20off%20anyone%2C%20whether%20it's%20for%20tariffs%20or%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20very%20small%2C%20but%20to%20me%2C%20the%20biggest%20accomplishment%20is%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20keep%20everyone%20through%20this%20tremendous%20uncertainty.%20I'm%20very%20proud%20of%20myself%20as%20a%20CEO%20for%20getting%20us%20through%20the%20most%20rocky%20time%20in%20our%20seven-year%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKush%20Desai%2C%20a%20White%20House%20spokesperson%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EPresident%20Trump%20has%20been%20clear%3A%20if%20you%20make%20your%20product%20in%20America%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20tariffs.%20Industry%20leaders%20ranging%20from%20TSMC%20to%20Apple%20to%20Stellantis%20have%20already%20responded%20with%20trillions%20in%20historic%20investment%20commitments%20to%20make%20and%20hire%20in%20America.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-shares-exerience-tariffs-pivoting-sales-overseas-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762426501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690aa7840be9845f2dc5bd15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-shares-exerience-tariffs-pivoting-sales-overseas-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Matthew%20Hassett%2C%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Loftie%2C%20pivoted%20his%20strategy%20amid%20US%20tariffs%2C%20opting%20for%20international%20expansion%20to%20maintain%20growth%20and%20stability.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-shares-exerience-tariffs-pivoting-sales-overseas-2025-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nithin%20Kamath%20Praises%20Groww%20IPO%2C%20Says%2020%25%20Applications%20From%20Zerodha%20Users%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Zerodha%20co-founder%20Nithin%20Kamath%20has%20congratulated%20Lalit%20Keshre%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20rival%20brokerage%20firm%20Groww%2C%20on%20their%20IPO.%20Kamath%20also%20said%20that%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20Groww%20IPO%20applications%20are%20coming%20from%20Zerodha%20customers.%22%2C