0that%20led%20to%20abandon%20the%20Financial%20Independence%2C%20Retire%20Early%20movement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrown%20no%20longer%20puts%20money%20into%20investment%20funds%20and%20works%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20in%20early%202019%20when%20I%20heard%20a%20news%20segment%20on%20the%20radio%20that%20people%20were%20retiring%20in%20their%2030s%20through%20a%20movement%20called%20FIRE%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-early-and-back-to-work-made-these-mistakes-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Independence%2C%20Retire%20Early%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20premise%20seemed%20simple%3A%20Live%20frugally%20and%20invest%20aggressively%20until%20you%20can%20live%20off%20your%20savings%20and%20the%20interest%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20immediately%20intrigued.%20Six%20years%20earlier%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20opened%20a%20wine%20store%20and%20bar%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20we're%20from%2C%20and%20were%20exhausted%20from%20the%20long%20hours.%20Not%20working%20unless%20I%20wanted%20to%20was%20appealing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202019%2C%20at%20age%2034%2C%20I%20started%20investing%20aggressively%2C%20and%20for%2015%20months%2C%20it%20was%20practically%20all%20I%20thought%20about.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20already%20had%20around%20%C2%A3233%2C000%20from%20previous%20savings%20and%20the%20equity%20in%20our%20house%2C%20which%20we%20planned%20to%20sell%20one%20day%2C%20along%20with%20our%20business%2C%20to%20travel%20full-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20just%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20I'd%20find%20myself%20in%20a%20moral%20dilemma%20over%20my%20investments%2C%20which%20would%20see%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffire-movement-quit-millennial-after-saving-over-half-income-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equit%20FIRE%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e772c2cd-3656-4868-bc60-0fbd0d042eab%5C%22%3EFIRE%20helped%20me%20quit%20my%20business%20and%20leave%20the%20UK%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETraveling%20full-time%20always%20felt%20like%20a%20pipe%20dream%2C%20but%20seeing%20how%20much%20money%20we%20already%20had%20in%20assets%20encouraged%20me%20to%20jump%20into%20investing.%20Unlike%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-calculated-the-cost-to-retire-early-in-san-francisco-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFIRE%20advocates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20wasn't%20aiming%20to%20save%20a%20specific%20amount%3B%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20see%20how%20much%20I%20could%20accumulate%2C%20and%20poured%20every%20spare%20penny%20into%20index%20funds.%20Income%20from%20our%20hospitality%20business%20wasn't%20consistent%2C%20but%20we%20kept%20our%20monthly%20outgoings%20low%20so%20we%20could%20invest%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202020%2C%20we%20accepted%20an%20offer%20to%20buy%20our%20business%2C%20which%20allowed%20us%20to%20inject%20even%20more%20cash%20into%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-invest-in-index-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eindex%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20sold%20our%20house%20and%20most%20of%20our%20belongings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20October%2C%20only%2015%20months%20after%20discovering%20FIRE%20and%20just%20weeks%20after%20completing%20our%20business%20sale%2C%20we%20said%20goodbye%20to%20the%20UK%20for%20a%20life%20of%20travel.%20Though%20we%20didn't%20feel%20like%20we%20had%20enough%20saved%20to%20stop%20working%20forever%2C%20we%20both%20wanted%20to%20take%20a%20break%20and%20figure%20out%20our%20future%20as%20we%20went.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223168%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Charlie%20Brown%20standing%20on%20a%20train%20station%20platform%20holding%20the%20handle%20of%20a%20red%20suitcase%20with%20wheels.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690a19a8c007ca8c2738329e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222380%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrown%20and%20her%20husband%20left%20the%20UK%20in%20October%202020.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Charlie%20Brown%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ae1b56c-11b3-4367-aa6a-25b078125ee3%5C%22%3EI%20felt%20freer%20than%20ever%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20long%20before%20I%20had%20doubts%20about%20my%20investment%20strategy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20be%20financially%20independent%20so%20I%20could%20sit%20on%20a%20beach%20all%20day%2C%20but%20to%20find%20time%20to%20live%20a%20meaningful%20life.%20Within%20a%20week%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-uk-to-us-i-struggle-with-loneliness-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleaving%20the%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20try%20freelance%20writing.%20I%20had%20wanted%20to%20rid%20myself%20of%20the%20stress%20of%20running%20a%20hospitality%20business%2C%20and%20writing%20enabled%20me%20to%20earn%20money%20and%20do%20meaningful%20work%20without%20burning%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20out%20living%20for%20five%20months%20in%20the%20small%20Spanish%20wine-making%20city%20of%20Logro%C3%B1o.%20Being%20in%20the%20wine%20trade%2C%20we%20were%20excited%20to%20be%20surrounded%20by%20wineries%2C%20and%20despite%20the%20COVID-era%20restrictions%2C%20we%20loved%20our%20new%20life%20there.%20Once%20the%20borders%20opened%20up%2C%20we%20spent%20the%20next%202.5%20years%20visiting%20various%20European%20countries%2C%20including%20Georgia%2C%20Italy%2C%20and%20Portugal%2C%20the%20latter%20being%20where%20we%20eventually%20settled%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20travels%2C%20my%20attitude%20toward%20FIRE%20began%20to%20change.%20Initially%2C%20I%20wasn't%20overly%20concerned%20with%20which%20companies%20I%20invested%20in%3B%20I%20just%20wanted%20bigger%20and%20bigger%20returns.%20But%20as%20time%20went%20on%2C%20I%20felt%20uncomfortable%20about%20where%20my%20money%20was%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20heard%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fethical-investing-anti-capitalist-financial-planner-2023-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eethical%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20began%20asking%20myself%20if%20the%20companies%20I'd%20invested%20in%20were%20contributing%20to%20a%20world%20I'd%20want%20to%20inhabit.%20Increasingly%2C%20the%20answer%20was%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20I%20slowly%20moved%20as%20many%20investments%20as%20I%20could%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fesg-investing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%2C%20social%2C%20and%20governance%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20exclude%20ethically%20questionable%20industries%20like%20tobacco%20or%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20still%20didn't%20agree%20with%20the%20ethics%20of%20some%20of%20the%20companies%20in%20these%20funds%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20because%20of%20how%20they%20treated%20staff%20or%20the%20actions%20of%20their%20CEOs.%20I%20felt%20guilty%20about%20profiting%20off%20them%2C%20but%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da3d998e-8354-4ecc-8867-9903f01310de%5C%22%3EI've%20abandoned%20the%20FIRE%20movement%20for%20a%20different%20dream%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20June%202025%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fthe-point-of-view%2Fmy-name-is-charlie-and-i-am-a-recovering-financial-independence-retire-early-addict-c69aaafea955%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhen%20I%20wrote%20on%20Medium%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20ethical%20implications%20of%20personal%20investment%20strategies%2C%20that%20I%20realized%20I%20could%20do%20more%20to%20practice%20what%20I%20preached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I've%20stopped%20moving%20money%20into%20investment%20funds%2C%20and%20I'm%20looking%20into%20different%20ways%20to%20approach%20my%20finances%2C%20including%20a%20potential%20investment%20in%20a%20new%20business%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20can%20run%20together.%20It's%20scary%20because%20it%20means%20spending%20my%20savings%20and%20depleting%20my%20safety%20net%2C%20but%20I%20want%20to%20feel%20comfortable%20with%20where%20I%20invest%20my%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20instead%20of%20retiring%20early%2C%20I%20envision%20a%20future%20of%20writing%20and%20making%20wine%20with%20my%20husband%20in%20Portugal.%20Although%20my%20income%20as%20a%20writer%20can%20fluctuate%2C%20I'm%20glad%20I%20can%20write%20about%20important%20issues%20and%20do%20something%20I%20truly%20care%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20the%20FIRE%20movement%20was%20a%20double-edged%20sword.%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20where%20I%20am%20today%20in%20my%20career%20and%20life%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewithout%20it%2C%20but%20I'd%20no%20longer%20recommend%20it%20as%20an%20investment%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20experience%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Echasing%20early%20retirement%20meant%20prioritizing%20growth%20and%20profits%20over%20pretty%20much%20anything%20else%2C%20from%20where%20your%20money%20is%20invested%20to%20fully%20enjoying%20your%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20it's%20much%20more%20fun%20to%20work%20than%20to%20retire%20when%20you%20have%20a%20meaningful%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20trying%20to%20reach%20FIRE%3F%20Contact%20the%20editor%2C%20Charissa%20Cheong%2C%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffire-movement-years-quit-job-travel-felt-guilty-ethical-investing-202