%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2275d81003-d038-43c5-a787-09d8c88e20b8%5C%22%3EPrivate%20money%20lending%20earns%20them%20double-digit%20returns%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202025%2C%20the%20couple%20started%20lending%20money%20to%20other%20real%20estate%20investors%20and%20charging%20interest%20on%20the%20loan.%20This%20is%20known%20as%20private%20money%20lending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20we'd%20always%20been%20on%20the%20receiving%20end.%20We%20were%20the%20borrowers%20of%20private%20money%2C%20and%20so%20we%20understood%20conceptually%20how%20it%20worked%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Josh.%20%26quot%3BWe%20couldn't%20have%20imagined%20being%20in%20a%20place%20where%20we%20had%20%24200%2C000%20of%20capital%20that%20we%20could%20invest%20in%20deals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20started%20with%20a%20smaller%20deal%2C%20lending%20an%20investor%20%2415%2C000.%20Their%20second%20deal%20was%20a%20%24100%2C000%20loan%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20some%20industry%20standards%3A%20In%20the%20private%20money%20lending%20world%2C%2010%20to%2012%25%20interest%20is%20very%20common.%20That's%20the%20baseline%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20The%20lender%20primarily%20determines%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20loan%2C%20and%20these%20terms%20vary%20from%20one%20private%20lender%20to%20another.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20if%20it's%20a%20six-month%20loan%2C%20you'll%20get%2012%25.%20If%20it's%20a%20three-month%20loan%2C%20you%20might%20charge%2015%25%20because%20it's%20so%20much%20shorter%20and%20you%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20get%20a%20good%20return%20on%20your%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20to%20generating%20passive%20income%20this%20way%20is%20vetting%20both%20the%20borrower%20and%20the%20deal%20they're%20pursuing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20you%20do%20it%20properly%20with%20a%20vetted%20borrower%20with%20a%20good%20track%20record%2C%20it's%20literally%2030%20minutes%20of%20work%20one%20time%2C%20and%20then%20we'll%20get%20our%20money%20back%20in%20six%20months%2C%20plus%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Josh.%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20us%2030%20minutes%20driving%20to%20the%20bank%2C%20wiring%20the%20funds%2C%20and%20then%20the%20investor%20that%20is%20borrowing%20the%20money%20sends%20us%20updates%2C%20and%20that's%20the%20extent%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a832c8ca-997f-482e-8698-382c6578cb9a%5C%22%3E14%20long-term%20units%20bring%20in%20monthly%20rental%20income%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Lupos%2C%20who%20got%20their%20foot%20in%20the%20real%20estate%20door%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-how-to-buy-mortgage-tips-small-salary-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurchasing%20and%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20duplex%2C%20manage%2014%20long-term%20rental%20units%20in%20upstate%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20plan%20to%20eventually%20add%20more%20rentals%2C%20but%2C%20for%20now%2C%20they're%20focusing%20on%20optimizing%20their%20current%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20experience%2C%20it%20takes%20five%20to%20seven%20years%20for%20a%20property%20to%20get%20to%20that%20point%20where%20it's%20really%20generating%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Josh.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20a%20lot%20of%20times%20when%20you're%20buying%20a%20property%2C%20maybe%20the%20rents%20are%20below%20market%2C%20maybe%20the%20property%20needs%20some%20work%2C%20there%20are%20onboarding%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20but%20give%20it%20five%20years%20and%20that%20thing%20is%20now%20a%20well-oiled%20machine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20their%20real%20estate%20has%20been%20purchased%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20instead%20of%20aggressively%20continuing%20to%20try%20to%20buy%20more%2C%20I%20know%20we%20have%20thousands%20upon%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20a%20month%20of%20untapped%20income%2C%20but%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20time.%20We%20have%20to%20continue%20to%20upgrade%20the%20properties%2C%20fix%20the%20properties%2C%20increase%20the%20rent%2C%20and%20so%20on%20and%20so%20forth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20also%20planning%20on%20paying%20off%20some%20of%20their%20mortgages%20early%2C%20which%20could%20%26quot%3Bunlock%20another%20%2425%2C000%20to%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20cash%20flow%2C%20just%20from%20not%20having%20mortgages%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20real%20estate%20investment%20strategy%20is%20generally%20a%20buy-and-hold%20approach.%20However%2C%20they%20did%20sell%20one%20property%20in%20their%20portfolio%20in%202025%20and%20profited%20generously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20%24150%2C000%20duplex%20that%20we%20bought%20in%202020%2C%20we%20recently%20just%20sold%20for%20%24270%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20property%20that%20we%20bought%20in%202018%20for%20%24158%2C000%2C%20if%20we%20sold%20it%2C%20we%20probably%20get%20close%20to%20%24300%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Josh.%20%26quot%3BNot%20every%20property%20we%20own%20has%20doubled%20in%20value%2C%20but%20many%20of%20them%20are%2040%20to%2050%25%20more%20valuable%20than%20they%20were%20when%20we%20first%20purchased%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retirement-financial-independence-investment-strategy-fire-movement-passive-income-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762424101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690bc309513c94655a3db070%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-retirement-financial-independence-investment-strategy-fire-movement-passive-income-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI%20thought%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20seven-%20to%2010-year%20journey%20to%20get%20here%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20about%20a%20four-year%20sprint%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20ear