or%20veterans%2C%26quot%3B%20Vargas%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Collins'%20efforts.%20Von%20Letkemann%20shared%20that%20he%20understood%20the%20criticism.%20%26quot%3BEveryone's%20heart%20was%20in%20the%20right%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20gray%2C%20ambiguous%20space%20that's%20hard%20to%20navigate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDunlap%20declined%20to%20comment%20and%20referred%20Business%20Insider%20to%20the%20Marine%20Corps.%20The%20Marine%20Corps%20did%20not%20provide%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReviews%20of%20all%20troops'%20social%20media%20accounts%20intensified%20after%20the%20September%2010%20killing%20of%20conservative%20activist%20Charlie%20Kirk.%20In%20the%20days%20that%20followed%2C%20many%20troops'%20posts%20drew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-anti-woke-revolt-revolt-troops-crosshairs-trump-hegseth-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eswift%20and%20intense%20scrutiny%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20message%20last%20week%2C%20Navy%20Secretary%20John%20Phelan%20warned%20sailors%20and%20Marines%20that%20their%20activity%20online%20would%20be%20reviewed%20for%20potential%20political%20content.%20Troops%20may%20reference%20their%20rank%20or%20wear%20uniforms%20on%20personal%20accounts%20as%20long%20as%20the%20posts%20are%20not%20made%20in%20an%20official%20capacity%2C%20the%20message%20said.%20It%20also%20encouraged%20troops%20to%20%26quot%3Brefrain%26quot%3B%20from%20discussions%20or%20mention%20of%20government%20and%20military%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENavy%20officials%20declined%20to%20answer%20Business%20Insider's%20question%20on%20whether%20more%20guidance%20would%20be%20issued%20regarding%20ethical%20concerns%2C%20citing%20the%20ongoing%20government%20shutdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20warn%20the%20overlap%20between%20influencers%20and%20political%20figures%20could%20erode%20the%20military's%20apolitical%20ethos%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20as%20social%20media%20stars%20gain%20special%20access%20to%20policymakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20should%20all%20be%20concerned%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20government%20could%20decide%20to%20exert%20control%20over%20influencers'%20messaging%2C%20Center%20for%20a%20New%20American%20Security%20senior%20fellow%20Jason%20Dempsey%20said.%20The%20government%20could%20say%2C%20%26quot%3B'We%20don't%20want%20authentic%20voices%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2230d56bc8-87b1-4a2d-a8d0-ed9363fc8cf8%5C%22%3EInfluencers%20are%20benefitting%20financially%20from%20their%20Pentagon%20ties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20troops%20post%20content%20that%20boosts%20the%20military's%20image%2C%20they%20risk%20being%20accused%20of%20propaganda.%20If%20they%20speak%20too%20freely%20or%20provocatively%2C%20they%20risk%20drawing%20the%20ire%20of%20commanders%20or%20fellow%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20concern%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20is%20helping%20boost%20certain%20influencers'%20income.%20The%20%26quot%3BCreative%20Reserve%26quot%3B%20influencers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20gained%20exposure%20through%20their%20ties%20to%20the%20Pentagon%20program%2C%20Saling%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20exposure%20cuts%20both%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Army%20has%20benefited%20from%20their%20posts%2C%20which%20officials%20estimated%20to%20reach%2040%20million%20views%20during%20the%20Army's%20250th%20birthday%20celebration%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20comparison%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-college-athletes-are-getting-paid-from-nil-endorsement-deals%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20athletes%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20instructive.%20Since%202021%2C%20the%20NCAA%20has%20allowed%20players%20to%20earn%20money%20from%20their%20name%2C%20image%2C%20and%20likeness%20(NIL)%2C%20reflecting%20a%20wider%20cultural%20shift%20in%20how%20Americans%20define%20work%2C%20personal%20value%2C%20and%20self-promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20something%20the%20military%20may%20have%20to%20reckon%20with.%20%26quot%3BI'd%20say%20the%20culture%20in%20the%20DoD%20is%20that%20if%20you%20have%20put%20anywhere%20in%20there%20that%20you%20are%20in%20the%20Army%2C%20then%20that's%20ours%2C%26quot%3B%20Saling%20said%20of%20social%20media%20content%20and%20NIL%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20social%20media%20offers%20some%20service%20members%20a%20path%20to%20extra%20income%20%E2%80%94%20even%20as%20it%20puts%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20violating%20rules%20that%20may%20be%20out%20of%20sync%20with%20modern%20realities.%20The%20zeitgeist%20of%20Americans'%20desire%20for%20autonomy%2C%20even%20in%20an%20institution%20as%20hierarchical%20as%20the%20military%2C%20means%20that%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20Army%2C%20talent%20management%20must%20now%20consider%20the%20soldier%20as%20an%20individual%2C%20said%20Saling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20policy%20updates%2C%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20culture%20updates%20that%20have%20to%20happen%20because%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-influencers-social-media-pentagon-ethics-policy-gray-area-2025-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1762423201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69090b2ac007ca8c273824c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-influencers-social-media-pentagon-ethics-policy-gray-area-2025-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Military%20influencers%20are%20all%20over%20social%20media%2C%20posting%20daily%20military%20life%2C%20or%20political%20or%20sexual%20content.%20It's%20causing%20a%20headache%20for%20the%20Pentagon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kbaker%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Baker)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmilitary-influencers-